# Notes:
# - Set ADMIN_API_KEY in Cloud Run environment variables, not in committed files.
# - Use a long random ADMIN_API_KEY value.
# - Frontend stores the admin key only in browser localStorage after an admin enters it manually.
# - OpenAI is optional only.
# - Local model support is future-ready and can stay disabled.
# - BUILDER_STORAGE_MODE=cloud uses Google Cloud Storage with Cloud Run default credentials.
# - Set GCS_BUCKET_NAME and GOOGLE_CLOUD_PROJECT in Cloud Run only when cloud JSON/JSONL storage is ready.
# - Firestore uses the Cloud Run service account on Google Cloud for legacy memory if enabled.
# - BACKEND_CORS_ORIGINS is comma-separated and should include the deployed frontend URL plus local dev origins if needed.
# - Do not commit secrets, passwords, tokens, API keys, or service account JSON.
# - Do not put secrets in the frontend.
# - Gmail/Drive OAuth and live search are future-ready only until real connectors are added.
# LIVE_SEARCH_PROVIDER examples: duckduckgo, brave, bing, serpapi, generic_json.
# DuckDuckGo does not require an API key; Brave/Bing/SerpAPI do and must be set only in backend Cloud Run env vars.
# Existing cloud storage can use STORAGE_MODE=firestore with FIRESTORE_ENABLED=true and GCP_PROJECT_ID, or BUILDER_STORAGE_MODE=cloud with GCS_BUCKET_NAME.
